author: John Kennedy
title: Florida Medicaid hits 4 million milestone
text:
Florida is hitting a milestone this year that may raise questions about the depth of the state’s economic recovery under Gov. Rick Scott.
A record more than 4 million Floridians — about 20 percent of the state’s population — will have health coverage provided by Medicaid this year, the state-federal program helping low-income families, the elderly and disabled.
